#RACHAELRAYSHOW says goodbye to an incredible game changing 17 season run today. Having the opportunity to join the show’s amazing team for segments over the past few years has been an unbelievable highlight!  From movie / TV talk (Rachael’s a legit fan), puppy weight loss 😅, Royal weddings, heartwarming holiday stories….there is nothing Rachael can’t tackle!  I walk away with unforgettable moments, conversations and laughs.  My biggest takeaway will always be observing, first hand, the skill of one of the queens of talk. Rachael’s ability to connect with her audience with emotion - from ANY subject matter - always struck me as remarkable. A master of the craft who will be missed every day!  All the best in your next adventures @rachaelray 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼🎉🎉🎉
And to @rsoldinger and team - thank you!

Alllll the feels over losing this cat. I got this girl and her sister from a rescue in Long Beach when they were just tiny little kittens playing in a cage. I got them for Tara before we were engaged.  They almost died from a serious fever a couple weeks later. We got thru that together and fell in love with Boo and Bella. I’ve always said Boo is our cat that acts like a dog - always cuddling up, in the middle of the action, talks to you until you give her attention, little fat curious happy cat. She symbolizes so much for us - 17 years of life change, dramatic shifts, marriage, kids, moving across the country, flights, road trips…we have more history with her than most friends. She leaves a huge void in our family, but we’ll always cherish the time and memories. ❤️
